Commentary Text: Murugan Ashwin to Narine, out Caught by de Grandhomme at long-off!!.. and Murugan Ashwin strikes with his first ball. This was tossed up nicely outside off, right in Narine's hitting zone, he took up the bait and was looking to cream it back over the bowler's head. The bat turned in his hands at the point of impact, he ended up slicing it high and towards long-off. de Grandhomme completes a fine catch. He had to make sure that he didn't step onto the ropes as he completed the catch - which he did. Relief for RCB and Chinnaswamy finds its voice back. Narine c de Grandhomme b Murugan Ashwin 27(19) [4s-3 6s-1]

Commentary Text: U Yadav to Narine, 1 run, top-edge and safe, is it going to be Narine's night? Banged in short and at the stumps, he was in no position on the pull, got it high off the bat and lobbed towards short mid-wicket. Perhaps was Umesh's catch, but he was late to turn back and can't get across to the ball. I have seen a couple of replays and Umesh seemed to have slipped while turning back. That cost him the momentum and the chance to go for the catch
